Ad Text:
About Us

At Agile Insights, we are passionate about empowering organisations to transform through the power of Data & AI. We work with global brands and leading organisations to deliver innovative solutions that solve real business challenges. We have a fantastic, long-standing relationship with Microsoft. We are extremely proud to be a Microsoft Solutions Specialist for four competencies including: Data Analytics and AI, Azure and Digital & App Innovation.

Your Role

Organisations in every industry are looking to AI technologies to solve a range of business problems and improve efficiency and quality across the board. As a Principal AI Consultant, you will play a pivotal role in designing, building, and deploying AI infused applications on Azure using services like Azure OpenAI, Azure AI Search and Azure Cognitive Services (vision, speech, language).

You will work with business stakeholders and executives to paint the art of the possible, help them understand where AI can help their organisations innovate, prioritize AI use cases based on business impact and feasibility, and build roadmaps to successful project delivery. You will work closely with customer business and technical teams to architect and deliver the solution. You’ll take the project through architecture and security reviews, document the solution and ensure successful hand-over to customer technical teams.

You will Bring

Previous experience in Principal-level consulting roles
Consulting skills – presales, workshop facilitation and stakeholder management
Ability to produce detailed technical documentation
Hands-on-keyboard software development experience
Real-world Azure apps and/or integration experience
Passion for AI and cloud technologies

Key responsibilities:

Solution Delivery

Paint the ‘art of the possible’ with the client, understand their business and requirements and translate that vision into an AI solution. Own the end-to-end delivery of Enterprise AI solutions to production including managing internal and external stakeholders, project budget, timeline and a quality enterprise AI solution. Responsible for the code-quality, infrastructure, security, scalability and maintainability of the solution and shepherding the solution through enterprise CAB and ARB processes.

Workshops and Enablement

Facilitate envisioning sessions and hands-on workshops to explore AI opportunities for clients, showcasing the potential of Microsoft AI technologies.

Technical Leadership

Provide expert guidance on Microsoft OpenAI and related technologies, serving as a trusted advisor to clients and internal teams.  Mentor and inspire technical teams, fostering a culture of continuous learning and innovation.  Stay ahead of emerging trends and advancements in AI and Microsoft technologies, incorporating them into Agile Insights’ offerings.

Consulting & Client Engagement

Collaborate with clients to understand their unique challenges, translating business requirements into technical solutions.  Build strong relationships with stakeholders, ensuring alignment and satisfaction throughout the engagement lifecycle.  Provide thought leadership through whitepapers, blogs, and presentations, positioning Agile Insights as a leading Microsoft Data & AI partner. 

IP Creation and Innovation

Drive the development of proprietary accelerators, frameworks, and reusable assets to enhance delivery efficiency and solution impact.  Work with Agile Insights' teams to design and launch AI-powered products aligned with market needs and Microsoft’s ecosystem.  Collaborate with Microsoft and other partners to secure funding and co-develop innovative solutions. 

Practice Growth

Support pre-sales efforts by crafting proposals, developing demos, and estimating project delivery costs.  Contribute to Agile Insights' thought leadership by participating in industry events, panels, and conferences.  Build and nurture a network of client relationships, identifying opportunities to expand Agile Insights’ presence in the market. 

What We’re Looking For:

Background in technical consulting & delivery roles.
Experience building web applications on Azure in .NET (or Python) and JavaScript frameworks (React Preferred).
Experience with LLM development (OpenAI, Semantic Kernel, Langchain, etc) Knowledge of the wider Azure AI landscape and tools (e.g. Azure AI Search, Cognitive Services)
Experience designing and architecting applications using Azure cloud-native components including AppService, Functions, LogicApps, etc.
Azure Integration Services experience will be highly valued.
Strong knowledge of data technologies including SQL, Cosmos and Fabric
Broad knowledge of cloud-based architectures and principles (security, networking)
Keen for a fast-paced environment with the opportunities to learn, grow and be exposed to a variety of problems, clients and technologies.
Ability to understand client requirements and transform into working solutions.
Ability to work remotely via Microsoft Teams
Aptitude for critical and analytical thinking, as well as the capacity to leverage out-of-the box solutions
Employment basis: Permanent, full time, Hybrid, ideally located in Sydney, Brisbane, Adelaide or Melbourne.

What’s In It for You?

At Agile Insights, we believe in nurturing talent and creating a supportive, flexible, and rewarding workplace. Here’s what you can look forward to:

Wellbeing: Access to hybrid work arrangements, an Employee Assistance Program, and an individualised gym and wellbeing program.
Flexibility: Work from anywhere for up to 6 weeks per year.
Professional Development: Additional paid leave for certifications and exams, with Agile-sponsored training programs for Microsoft and Databricks certifications.
Team Engagement: Enjoy regular team meetups, including state-based gatherings and an annual all-company event.
Equipment & Hardware: Receive an allowance for your home office setup and a 2-year equipment incentive.
Salary Packaging: Access novated leasing services for tax-effective car purchases.
Learning Resources: Expand your skills with access to our digital library and learning platforms. Opportunity to work with some of the best developers in the business including one on one mentoring with senior consultants.

Why Agile Insights?

Work with some of the largest clients and global brands across diverse industries. Be part of a fast-growing, award-winning team passionate about transforming organisations with Data & AI. Thrive in a friendly start-up culture that values innovation, collaboration, and work-life balance.

Ready to Lead with Us?

If you’re passionate about analytics, consulting, and community engagement, we’d love to hear from you.

Apply now to join Agile Insights and take your career to the next level!

No Agencies - No overseas applications - Must be in Australia and have full work rights

Job Title: Senior Engineer - Monitoring and Observability Optimization - Hawthorn East
Ad Text:
We've been trusted to serve Aussie communities since 1914 and grown to become a top 30-listed on the ASX with 120,000 team members and a portfolio of iconic brands. At Coles Group, you'll not only get to make a difference to millions of Aussie lives—you'll also get to see your impact.

About the team

Technology is the backbone of our business. Every day, our teams solve complex problems, the solutions help thousands of our fellow team members succeed and makes millions of customers’ lives easier. 

About the role 

A permanent opportunity of a Senior Systems Engineer Observability is now available at the Coles Group.  

Reporting into the Platform Manager – Monitoring and Observability, this role will primarily be responsible for in maintaining an efficient Observability and AiOps platform by creating and managing policies & framework, setup optimisation rules, and manage license subscriptions/costs. 

Key responsibilities will include 
Primary SME and provide technical and operational support for Splunk Cloud/ITSI optimisation (searches, storage, retention, policies, etc.) 
Primary SME and provide technical and operational support for Splunk Observability Cloud optimisation (health rules, alerts, scripts, etc.) 
Primary SME and provide technical and operational support for UiPath/Ansible automation optimisation (BOTs, license, scripts) 
License Manager for all tools managed by M&O, purchases/renewals. 
Maintain compliance with best practise guidelines and guardrails to optimise costs. 
Create ITSI services, KPIs, and notable events to provide comprehensive visibility into IT operations. 
Collaborate with internal stakeholders and subject matter experts to gather requirements and help support evolving business needs. 
Assist with performing regular system maintenance activities, including patching, upgrades, and performance tuning, to ensure optimal performance and stability of the platform. 
Contribute to developing and maintaining the required operational documentation, including standard operating procedures, technical guides, and knowledge base articles, to facilitate efficient troubleshooting and knowledge sharing. 
Collaborate with the Splunk technical resources and account team to address technical issues and implement enhancements or bug fixes. 
Act as a liaison between the support team and other IT teams, assisting with incident resolution, change management, and problem management processes. 
Help build a strong brand for our helping to build a strong brand for our frontline Technology function and M&O, AiOps platform. 

About you & your skills 
Extensive years of hands-on technical experience in implementing and supporting Splunk Cloud and ITSI platforms. 
Strong background in Splunk cloud/ITSI optimisation techniques (searches, storage, retention, policies, etc.) 
Strong background in UiPath/Ansible automation optimisation techniques 
Strong background in Splunk Observability Cloud optimisation techniques 
Experience in Splunk, UiPath license management 
Comprehensive experience in various data sources (monitoring tools, ticketing systems, logs, metrics, traces, etc.) 
Extensive experience in Tech to Business Service Tree mapping. 
Extensive experience in Event Management, workflow development. 
Experience in implementing & supporting RPA based automation (UiPath, Power Automate, etc.) – desirable. 
Experience in implementing & supporting Infrastructure IT Operations based automation (Ansible) – desirable. 
Hands on experience with automating process, optimising workflows and integrations.   
Experience in delivery principles and coding standards. 
Experience in scripting – PowerShell, Python, etc. 
Strong knowledge of CI/CD, bitbucket. 
Experience helping support groups and technology teams’ self-help and get the most out of the Splunk platform. 
Technical experience in supporting AiOps, TechOps. 
Advanced understanding of all aspects of the broader operational environment (i.e.. processes, procedures, associated toolsets, operating systems, etc.). 
Experience with cloud infrastructure (Azure, GCP, AWS). 
Experience in monitoring containerised solutions. 
Proven capabilities in vendor, partner and stakeholder relationship management including the monitoring and maintenance of outsource agreements and project delivery to agreed service levels and timeframes. 

Commercial Skills and Formal Qualifications 
Splunk ITSI Certification. 
ITIL Certification. 
Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to analyse and resolve complex technical issues. 
Strong communication skills, both written and verbal, with the ability to effectively collaborate with cross-functional teams and stakeholders. 
Self-starter, Self-motivated and proactive, with the ability to work independently and prioritize tasks in a fast-paced environment. 
Ability to articulate solutions and influence others-simply. 

Take your next step into something bigger, apply now!

With us it’s not about the discounts (although you do get those), it’s about joining a team where your wellbeing and professional development is invested in and celebrating your contributions is the norm. And because everyone leads unique lives, we offer flexible work including work from home, additional leave, and parental leave entitlements. 

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that’s just as diverse, inclusive, and welcoming as the communities we serve. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation, and gender identities. 

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process' section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au.

About Us 

At Sportsbet, we’re all about bringing excitement to life for our 2.4 million customers. As part of the global Flutter Group, we’re a tight-knit team of 1,300 in Melbourne, Sydney, and Darwin, passionate about challenging the status quo. We’re proud to be recognized as one of LinkedIn’s Top 25 Companies and one of the Top 10 Workplaces for Women. 

We’re an inclusive employer who celebrates diversity and is committed to helping you thrive. Whether you’re looking for flexibility, career growth, or a supportive environment, we’re here to help you succeed. 

Committed To Responsible Gambling 

Our commitment to responsible gambling is genuine and demonstrated through the wide range of responsible gambling initiatives and tools. 

We’re proud to be the leaders in responsible gambling in our industry, not just locally, but globally. 

About the Role

The Senior ML Engineer is a key role within Data Platforms, responsible for delivering innovative and sustainable data driven solutions contributing to Sportsbet having a competitive advantage in the Machine Learning domain within the quant space.

This is an exciting opportunity support our industry leading Data Science team, delivering cutting edge customer facing models into production and optimising their performance, along with contributing key capabilities back into our international Flutter brands for wider use. Your day could see you doing:

Build feature pipelines, model inference services, and monitoring tools.
Design and implement CI/CD pipelines with automated testing.
Standardise ML delivery patterns and best practices across teams.
Lead delivery estimation and ensure accountability for outcomes.
Identify and close gaps across DevOps, security, and operations.
Optimise ML systems for performance, reliability, and cost.
Own what you build — monitor, troubleshoot, and resolve production issues.
Drive automation and continuous improvement across ML workflows.
Share expertise and promote innovation.

About You

You have the ability to ask the right questions with an eye for detail with an interest in building price assurance framework tools. We would like you to have:

Proficiency in developing software models in Rust / Python / C family, leveraging sub-model architectures to build modularised application in a solver / simulation-based application.
Strong expertise in designing low-latency application backed with demonstrable knowledge of concurrency, parallelisation, performance tuning, while enforcing memory safety
Strong experience leading the SDLC for Machine Learning and Data Science models, building ML pipelines, feature stores and containerisation utilising Docker / Kubernetes
Proven experience in designing, training, and validating machine learning models for real-time prediction tasks (e.g., regression, classification, time-series, anomaly detection).
Well-versed in model experimentation and evaluation techniques (e.g., A/B testing, back-testing, cross-validation, error analysis).
Familiarity with data models such as Data Vault, Kimball, and Medallion architecture (ideal but not essential)

Why You’ll Love Working Here

Along with a competitive salary and generous performance-based bonus, here’s some of our other benefits:

25 days annual leave (plus flexible working options)
$1050 work-from-home allowance
Access to outstanding career development programs, including expert-led internal training and external learning opportunities
Onsite concierge services, free meals, social events and access to the Sportsbet Salon
Generous parental leave and return-to-work benefits
Hack Days: Participate in our hack days, where creativity and collaboration lead to exciting new ideas and projects.


What’s the Green Tick Feeling?

Well, it’s different for everyone, yet unites us all. It’s the feeling you get when you succeed, no matter what success looks like to you. It could be developing your career, it could be working on an industry leading project, or it could be making it to school pick up in time. It's all the little and big things that make you feel like you’re thriving when working at Sportsbet. 

We’re an inclusive employer who welcomes you for who you are, as you are – so, if you require adjustments to the recruitment process, please let us know in your application. We also know flex means different things to different people, so let us know how we can support you to be your best. 

We review applications quickly, so apply soon! Check out our Life@Sportsbet Instagram, LinkedIn, and careers website for more about our inclusive culture.

Ready for your Green Tick Feeling? Apply now.

When you choose AusNet, you’ll join genuine people working together, making Real. Progress

At AusNet, we’re the link between renewable energy sources and local communities, playing a key role in the clean energy transition and providing essential energy to every Victorian family.  AusNet’s gas network is an essential service for homes and businesses in Western Victoria and will remain a critical part of the energy system for decades to come.

Help us lead the way, while enriching your career with real people who encourage you to bring your best and make real impact – for your career, our communities, and Australia’s cleaner energy future.

Purposeful work with genuinely good people. That’s refreshing.

The future of gas is evolving. As owners of both electricity and gas networks in Victoria, we have a front row seat to how customer behaviour is changing and how the energy system will change, and the gas network will continue to play a critical role through this dynamic period. We need strategic thinkers to collaborate on maintaining a safe and reliable network, promoting price stability, and planning for our future role. As Strategy Lead, you’ll help shape this future - bringing insight, creativity, and influence to one of the most significant transitions in Australia’s energy landscape.

This role will deliver real outcomes, including but not limited to:

Developing a long-term strategic agenda for the gas network and pathway to implementation.

Undertaking rigorous research and analysis to assess risks and opportunities.

Driving execution of strategic initiatives and responding rapidly to emerging issues.

Preparing insights and recommendations for the Board and Executive Leadership Team.

You don’t need to check every box; however, we are looking for a good combination of:

Demonstrated experience in strategy roles (consulting, corporate strategy, or similar).

Strong analytical and financial modelling skills, with advanced Excel and PowerPoint capability.

Excellent communication skills and ability to influence at executive level.

Energy sector experience is a plus, but not essential.

A real place to belong

We celebrate unique voices, refreshing perspectives and diversity in our team. Engage and connect through our social club, family day, wide range of events or by joining one of our Employee Network Groups.

We believe in more than just competitive pay. Here’s what sets us apart:

Development: Exposure to AusNet’s ELT, plus mentoring from a leader with top-tier consulting experience.

Flexibility: Hybrid work and flexible hours to help balance work and life.

Leave: Generous 14 weeks paid parental leave, with no minimum service.

Community Giving: A paid day to volunteer for a cause that matters to you.

Perks: Purchased leave, income protection insurance, novated leasing, corporate discounts, private health cover discounts and more.

As an industry in transformation, we’re excited by the possibilities ahead.

So, if you’re passionate about our purpose and committed to making real progress, bring your energy and join AusNet. Together, we can shape a new way forward.

Ad Text:
Shape Your World

At Alcoa, you will become an essential part of our purpose: to turn raw potential into real progress. The way we see it, every Alcoan is a work-shaper, team-shaper, idea-shaper & world-shaper.

As a leader within Alcoa, you can help fulfill our purpose and realise our vision to build a legacy of excellence for future generations. Be part of the team that is helping shape a better workplace with the flexibility and equal opportunities that help everyone thrive. You have the power to shape things and individuals to make them better.

About the Role

Are you a highly analytical, results-oriented leader with a passion for transforming complex global businesses? You could be our next Principal Performance Improvements expert, based directly at our Pinjarra Hub with regular travel to Huntly and Willowdale Mine Sites in Western Australia.

This senior role puts you at the forefront as an internal consultant and change agent, responsible for maximising efficiency, driving cost savings, and embedding operational excellence across our global footprint, specifically through dedicated work at Huntly and Willowdale.

You will enjoy a family-friendly Monday to Friday roster, providing a superb paid leisure day off every four weeks to help you realise a great work-life balance and have time for the things you love. You will report directly to the WA Mining ABS Manager, guaranteeing strong strategic alignment and senior visibility for your work.

Key responsibilities include

Lead high-impact local operational projects, directly optimising efficiency, throughput, and output at the Huntly and Willowdale Mine Sites.

Apply recognised continuous improvement methodologies (such as Lean, Six Sigma, and Agile) to diagnose operational constraints, eliminate waste, and deliver sustainable gains in safety, cost, and productivity.

Conduct complex data analysis to quantify potential benefits, establish clear, measurable targets (KPIs), and track project financial realisation post-implementation, ensuring validation and reporting of achieved business value.

Effectively collaborate with and influence senior leadership and cross-functional teams globally to organise support, manage change resistance, and drive project execution.

Coach and mentor site-based teams and functional leaders on continuous improvement principles, fostering a culture of ownership and data-driven decision-making throughout the operation.

This role places a strong emphasis on relationship building and engaging directly with our key stakeholders who are based on-site at our mining operations. While we are committed to offering some flexible working conditions, you may be expected to serve as the face of the Business Improvement operations, spending most of your time based on-site at Huntly or Willowdale, while leading a site-based improvement initiative or project.

What’s on offer

Attractive remuneration and variable bonus plan.

Flexible hybrid working options available.

Employee growth and development opportunities.

Parental leave support for all caregivers.

Paid employee volunteering hours within our community.

What you can bring to the role

Demonstrated success in performance improvement and continuous improvement (CI) within the mining, metals, or asset-intensive heavy industry sector.

Proven expertise in applying formal methodologies such as Lean, Six Sigma (Black Belt preferred), and Agile to solve complex operational and functional problems.

Exceptional ability to build trust and influence senior operational and functional leaders to secure project buy-in and drive successful change adoption.

Advanced analytical skills to conduct root-cause analysis, quantify opportunity value, and rigorously track and report on the financial realisation of project benefits.

Ability to seamlessly switch between defining high-level strategic global roadmaps and providing hands-on coaching and implementation support at the local site level.

Demonstrated success in leading organisational change initiatives and mentoring/upskilling site teams in CI practices to ensure improvements are sustained long-term.

Additional information

Interviews may progress prior to the closing date, although all applications will be considered.

You will only be contacted if you are shortlisted for an interview, this process can take up to four weeks from the closing date.

Be part of shaping our organisation and join us in building a legacy of excellence for future generations.

#LI-AA1

About the Location

Huntly is one of our two bauxite mines in Western Australia. Established in 1976 and located east of North Dandalup in WA, it is the world’s second largest bauxite mine, supplying ore to Alcoa’s Pinjarra alumina refinery. Bauxite ore from Alcoa’s Huntly and Willowdale mines helps to produce almost half of Australia’s alumina and approximately 19 per cent of Australia’s aluminium. Our workplace is an inclusive and respectful environment, where we embrace change, new ideas and equal opportunity to succeed. 

We are values led, vision driven and united by our purpose of transforming raw potential into real progress.  Our commitments to Inclusion, Diversity & Equity include providing trusting workplaces that are safe, respectful and inclusive of all individuals, free from discrimination, bullying and harassment and that our workplaces reflect the diversity of the communities in which we operate.    

This is a place where you are empowered to do your best work, be your authentic self, and feel a true sense of belonging. Come join us and shape your career!  

Your work. Your world. Shape them for the better.

This role offers the chance to be part of a multi-year initiative that is reshaping the Collections & Hardship business space, operating within a highly regulated environment and impact change to foster business readiness and change management. Be part of a significant enterprise-wide transformation that will provide extensive professional growth, Work within a highly regulated environment and enjoy flexible working arrangements




What you'll do:

As a Change Analyst, you will play an integral role in supporting one of the most ambitious transformation programmes within the banking sector. Your day-to-day responsibilities will involve working collaboratively with various teams to ensure that change initiatives are delivered smoothly and effectively. You will engage with stakeholders from different areas of the business, helping them navigate complex changes while maintaining compliance with strict regulatory standards. Your efforts will be crucial in preparing teams for new ways of working, facilitating open communication channels, and ensuring that every aspect of change is documented thoroughly. Success in this role will require you to balance multiple priorities under pressure while remaining focused on delivering positive outcomes for both the organisation and its customers.




Support the successful delivery of change initiatives across a large enterprise transformation platform, ensuring alignment with strategic objectives.
Collaborate closely with stakeholders in the Collections & Hardship business space to understand their needs and facilitate effective change adoption.
Operate within a highly APRA-regulated environment, maintaining rigorous standards for risk management, controls, and traceability throughout all change activities.
Work alongside both first and second line risk teams to identify potential risks associated with change initiatives and implement appropriate mitigation strategies.
Contribute to business readiness by preparing impacted teams for upcoming changes through clear communication, training sessions, and tailored support.



What you bring:

Your proven track record as a Change Analyst or similar role within large-scale transformation programmes will set you up for success in this position. You bring not only technical expertise but also exceptional interpersonal skills that enable you to build trust with stakeholders across the organisation. Your familiarity with risk management frameworks-especially those relevant to APRA regulations-will allow you to navigate complex compliance requirements confidently.


Demonstrated experience supporting large-scale transformation programmes within financial services or similarly regulated industries.
Proven ability to work collaboratively with diverse stakeholder groups to facilitate effective change adoption.
Strong understanding of risk management principles, particularly within APRA-regulated environments.
Excellent organisational skills with the ability to manage complex delivery timelines under pressure.
Outstanding written and verbal communication skills for documenting processes and engaging stakeholders at all levels.

What sets this company apart:

This organisation stands out as one of Australia's most respected financial institutions, renowned for its commitment to responsible banking practices and customer-centric innovation. Employees benefit from an inclusive culture where diversity is celebrated and every voice is heard. Flexible working arrangements empower staff to balance personal commitments with professional ambitions. The company invests heavily in ongoing training opportunities so that team members can continually develop their skills in response to industry changes. Supportive leadership encourages open dialogue about challenges faced during transformation projects while providing guidance rooted in deep sector expertise. Joining this team means becoming part of a network that values collaboration above all else-where your contributions are recognised as essential components of shared success.



What's next:

If you are ready to take on an impactful role where your collaborative spirit can truly shine, we encourage you to apply today!

Partner with stakeholders to embed data and AI ownership, governance practices  
Permanent Full-time Position, Sydney CBD location 
Hybrid working environment, attractive salary package 

About the Role 

In this role, you will establish, operate and advocate fit-for-purpose data and responsible AI frameworks, policies and best practices that enable effective and timely decisions on data and AI, aligned to legal, compliance, risk appetite and business value priorities  

Benefits 

A corporate wellbeing program with subsidised gym membership, free flu vaccinations and health check programs 
17.5% annual leave loading  
Comprehensive learning and development support aligned to icare’s Core Capabilities.  
Our People Awards - On-the-spot Recognition, Quarterly Values Awards & Our People Annual Awards 
Access to our Employee Assistance Program  

Duties 

It’s an exciting time at icare where no two days are the same; as a Manager, Data & AI Governance you will:

Work closely across whole of business, to establish and embed governance structures, data and AI ownership, and facilitate AI governance reviews ensuring they balance risk, value and compliance considerations and align with NSW Government frameworks and practices.  
Establish and embed data and AI risk management practices in partnership with Risk Management function, aligning with enterprise risk management frameworks and risk appetite.  
Design, embed and continuously adapt frameworks, policies and practices to cater for growing and innovative data, analytics and AI technologies and their usage in a changing legislative environment.

Atturra Data & Analytics are looking for a Lead / Senior Data Specialist to own the journey from legacy silos to a Unified Lakehouse on Databricks. Confident stakeholder engagement—from technical deep dives to board level briefings

Familiarity with cost optimisation and FinOps in cloud analytics environments.

* Conduct detailed change impact assessments, documenting impacts to processes, responsibilities and workflows.
* Develop and deliver communications tailored to various stakeholder groups, ensuring clear and consistent messaging about changes, benefits, timelines, and expectations.
* Analyse the differences between the legacy system and the new platform to identify key change areas and readiness gaps.
* Engage with various stakeholders, especially end users, to assess readiness, understand system usage, identify concerns, provide guidance, and gather feedback.
* Contribute to the development of training materials and participate in training activities.
* Assist with go-live activities, provide post-implementation support and coaching, and monitor adoption levels.

Essential Requirements for the role

* Must have experience with the role title of Change Analyst/Change Manager, with extensive experience designing and implementing change initiatives to support successful IT project/program outcomes, including technology-focused transformations.
* Strong experience engaging stakeholders to build relationships and support people through change.
* Proven experience developing and executing communication and training around changes to IT application.
* Organisational skills with the ability to manage multiple activities in a fast-paced project environment.
* Mix of Government and Private sector experience preferred. Ideally would have Government expeirence.

Salary starting from $152,074 (depending on experience) plus 15.4% superannuation
Permanent role
Applications close at 11:59pm AEST Wednesday, 17 December 2025

 

The team 

Our Registry & Intelligence team provide trusted data, insights and frontline services that help Australians make informed decisions and participate confidently in the economy. Establish reporting mechanisms, risk controls and compliance practices for data governance.
Provide expert advice on registry data governance and manage strategic relationships with key stakeholders.

 

About you

In addition, you will have:

Proven experience (5+ years) in data governance, risk or related functions.
Strong knowledge of data management tools, data architecture, metadata and governance frameworks.
Understanding of legal and policy frameworks for data strategy and compliance.
Experience managing data in regulated or commercial environments, leading teams and building stakeholder relationships.
Tertiary qualification in data science, technology, or business with a data governance focus.
Excellent communication skills with the ability to simplify complex concepts and influence decisions.

As the Audience & Growth Director of Entertainment, Audio, and News360, you will drive strategic growth by blending data storytelling and analytical thinking. This high-impact role focuses on increasing direct traffic and engaged reach across all multi-platform content. You must leverage insights, sharp news judgment, and technical skills to engage new and existing audiences.

Reporting to the Head of Entertainment, Multi-platform Audio and News360, you will lead acquisition and deep engagement efforts, implementing strategic innovation. Expertise in stakeholder management is key, liaising with editors across the wider business to maximize content discoverability. You'll be passionate about using data to anticipate audience trends and analysing performance to ensure the team is making insight-informed decisions.

Key Responsibilities:

Innovate, evolve and execute a strategy to grow discoverability of content across Entertainment, Multi-platform Audio and News360, and secure engaged reach for editorial brands and teams.

Ensure comprehensive audience data is kept, monitor performance across all platforms, and liaise with editorial and commercial leaders to provide and refine this data on a regular basis.

Work with key stakeholders across Entertainment, Multi-platform Audio and News360 to produce a multi-platform content distribution strategy that amplifies high-performing and original content for video, digital, audio, social (and print), utilising strong knowledge of SEO, sell angles and optimal publication times and dates, as well as highlighting key opportunities and strategy for resells to drive engagement and audience retention.

Attend daily news conference meetings on behalf of Entertainment, Multi-platform Audio and News360 and liaise with relevant news desks and digital editors across the wider business to keep key stakeholders informed of long-lead and short-lead content and daily news lists, highlighting key opportunities to harness direct traffic, engaged reach and new audience acquisition.

Identify opportunities to amplify content across our platforms and publications, basing your decisions on audience insights and analytics. This is a vital part of our digital media strategy and key to driving a sustainable and growing audience - now and in the future.

Drive optimisation of discoverability of content off-platform (e.g., newsletters, social media, etc.). Monitor and interpret content performance, delivering feedback and suggestions to relevant stakeholders.

Provide daily analytics and analyse performance reporting to the Head Of Entertainment, Multi-platform Audio and News360 and content directors within the department as well as commercial teams where required.

Continually be on the lookout for original avenues and unexpected arenas through which to acquire, retain and grow new audiences.

​Initiate and implement strategies to grow direct traffic and engagement and engaged audio/video/multiplatform reach for all content produced by the Entertainment, Multi-platform Audio and News360 team.

Who are you?

10+ Years Experience in media, including digital/multi-platform newsrooms and audience research/marketing analytics.

Essential Audio Experience: Previous background in audio or commercial radio is required.

Proven News Sense: Impeccable ability to identify key issues, package content, and change tone/voice across multiple brands.

Content Optimization Expert: Track record in curating, optimizing, and distributing compelling multi-platform content with strong knowledge of SEO and paid/organic growth strategies.

Advanced Analytics Skills: 10+ years of experience translating complex data (quantitative research, audience analysis) into actionable strategies.

Tool Proficiency: Experienced with survey and data tools including Excel, SQL, and Google Analytics.

Digital Marketing Acumen: Strong understanding of principles, strategies, and experience with social media, email marketing, and paid advertising.

Engagement Focused: Ability to optimize compelling headlines, captions, and titles for digital, video, audio, and social formats.

Cross-Functional Leader: Successfully led a team and collaborated across multiple departments (editorial, sales, production).

Exceptional Collaborator: Strong people skills, excellent communication, and stakeholder management comfortable presenting to all levels.

Strategic & Driven: Proven track record of delivering measurable audience growth through executed campaigns.

Adaptable & Proactive: Thrives in a fast-paced, "always on" news cycle, demonstrating strong planning, analytical, and problem-solving abilities.

Journalism Passion: Deep understanding of and passion for journalism, digital storytelling, and content innovation.

Independent Worker: Ability to work independently and as part of a team, managing multiple initiatives simultaneously.

Company description:



Snowy Hydro is a dynamic, integrated energy business that has been providing on-demand, reliable energy to Australia for generations. Snowy Hydro owns and operates a powerful combination of generation assets, including the mighty Snowy Mountains Scheme, gas and diesel plants, and contracted wind and solar energy. We also provide electricity and gas to about 1.5 million retail customers through our retail brands Red Energy and Lumo Energy.

A full-time position exists for a Strategic Analyst to join the Strategy Team in the Planning and Performance stream.



Job description:



The Strategic Analyst will support the ongoing performance and capability of Snowy Hydro's assets and operations and support strategic decision making to ensure we maintain our position and capability in a rapidly changing market. The role adds value by providing strategic perspective and analytical support for decision making processes associated with asset and operations strategy development, risk management and investment decision making. The Strategy Team supports key decision making inputs by linking technical engineering, operations, commercial and work execution strategies. This includes the development of requirements statements, asset life cycle models, and facility strategies to support the overarching Generation Business Plan. This includes extensive stakeholder engagement and front end communication across the business.

Key Responsibilities:

Support the development of the Generation Business Plan to ensure we're planned and ready to deliver our corporate objectives.
Support the development of Facility Strategies underpinned by life cycle and risk models to support capability, opportunities and investment plans.
Provide a key interface between technical engineering teams, strategy, planning and work execution teams to provide delivery assurance.
Help the business identity and realise value adding opportunities across our assets and operations.
Support broader business decision making through ad-hoc analysis and decision making support.
Collaborating with others to ensure the Strategic team can extract the information needed for investment decision-making, life cycle costing, and setting long-term delivery strategies.

About the location:

This role offers flexibility in location, with the opportunity to be based in our Cooma, Sydney, or Melbourne office (with a strong preference for Cooma). Relocation support will be offered for anyone wanting to relocate to Cooma. You will be supporting and collaborating with multidisciplinary teams across the business to achieve shared strategic objectives.

About you:

We're looking for a self-starter with a proven industry background, a firm understanding of asset and risk management and an understanding of high criticality operating and commercial environments. You'll need to be able to blend the need to provide strategic thinking, supporting analysis, stakeholder engagement and communication. This is not a technical role however a strong understanding of electrical, mechanical and civil assets in heavy industries is integral.

The person we are looking for should have the following capabilities:

An accomplished professional with a background (10+ years is ideal) in asset and business strategy, particularly within dynamic sectors like utilities, heavy industries, or mining.
A sound technical understanding of generation or similar heavy assets (engineering or trade background preferred)
A strong foundation in a business-related discipline (such as a tertiary qualification in commerce, engineering, or CA/CPA or equivalent).
A solid management reporting background alongside demonstrated analytical skills and proficiency in data manipulation.
Demonstrated leadership, excellent stakeholder engagement, and a collaborative approach.
Strong verbal and written communication skills are essential, you'll regularly be engaging with stakeholders from all parts of the business.
The ability to draw meaningful conclusions while working in the grey area.
Capable of working autonomously and meeting deadlines.

About our workforce:

Diversity and inclusion is important to us. Snowy Hydro has a culture of decency and inclusion, with a commitment to the health and wellbeing of our people and a supportive environment to ensure that everyone - regardless of background - feels included and can succeed. At Snowy Hydro, we recognise that we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each individual brings, and we believe in providing an environment that allows that uniqueness to thrive.

Snowy Hydro is proud to be an Equal Opportunity employer. We are committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provide accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are interested in applying for a role with Snowy Hydro and are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an email with your request to the Snowy Hydro recruitment team at recruitment@snowyhydro.com.au

Job Title: Technical Business Analyst - Banking - Data Segregation
Ad Text:
Technical Business Analyst - Banking Projects - Data Segregation
 

About the Role
We are seeking an experienced Technical Business Analyst to work on a data segregation project classifying and segregating structured and unstructured data.

We are specifically looking for technical data analyst that has worked on data segregation projects where a bank or financial institution is segregating data.  You will be responsible for researching, analysing, and documenting project requirements of this data segregation so that data can be siloed into its own structured area.
 
This role requires a sharp eye for detail, strong communication skills, and a technical mindset to safeguard data integrity while supporting critical banking initiatives.
We are seeking someone that is a technical BA in data segregation. You may have worked in bank or financial institution that has sold a division or integrated a new acquisition and integrated data. 


 
Key Responsibilities

Conduct research and analysis on data to segregate data to be isolated.
Work closely with business stakeholders, project managers, and technical teams to define clear requirements.
Ensure all changes are implemented on time and to budget.
Assess risks and dependencies to ensure that data is categorised effectively and does not cause crashes, disruptions, or corrupt data.
Maintain and validate system documentation, workflows, and test scenarios.
Liaise with quality assurance and development teams to ensure smooth integration with existing systems.
Provide ongoing support for post-implementation reviews and improvements.
About You

Proven experience as a technical Business Analyst with segregating data within the banking or financial services sector.
Strong technical understanding of core banking systems and related applications.
Excellent ability to analyse dependencies and identify potential risks or conflicts across programs.
Skilled in documentation, requirements gathering, and stakeholder communication.
Demonstrated track record in delivering projects on time, within budget, and to scope.
Familiarity with testing, system validation, and regulatory requirements in financial services.

If you are a technically strong Business Analyst who has looked at data segregation previously in a secure banking environment, we'd love to hear from you.
For more information, please email peter@employ.com.au

About the Strategy & Operations Team


The Strategy & Operations team at DoorDash is the driving force behind the In-Store business line’s long-term growth and operational excellence. We work cross-functionally to develop and execute key initiatives that align with In-Store's strategic goals, ensuring scalability, efficiency, and optimal performance across the organization. Our team is focused on leveraging data-driven insights, improving processes, and guiding business decisions that enhance customer experience and foster company-wide innovation.

About the Role


DoorDash is looking for a Senior Associate, Strategy & Operations to help own and execute our overarching business strategy in the APAC region. This is a high-impact role that will be pivotal in launching and scaling new initiatives, starting with our DoorDash Reservation Marketplace and scaling New Product Launches.

You will be the strategic right-hand to INTL GTM leadership and the Global Head of Strategy & Operations, In-Store, helping improve the regional business strategy, driving our local pricing and packaging strategy, and ensuring our operations can scale efficiently. As a Business Process Owner, you will champion project creation and execution, requiring you to dive deep into data and build consensus with cross-functional partners. The ideal candidate is a structured "first-principles" thinker who has a bias for action, thrives in ambiguity, and is obsessed with using data to drive results and achieve our goal of sustainable revenue growth.

What You'll Do

Strategic Analysis and Planning: Assist INTL leadership in developing the long-term strategic plan for APAC. You will work on problems of diverse scope where analysis requires the evaluation of identifiable factors, critical thinking, and creativity. This includes identifying new market opportunities, analyzing the competitive landscape, and crafting go-to-market processes.
Business Process Ownership & Project Management: Champion project creation, planning, and execution for pivotal initiatives. You will work closely with leadership and teams across Product, Sales, and Marketing, leveraging your analytical skills to identify challenges, develop solutions, and ensure successful project execution in line with our growth objectives. You will establish clear metrics for success and designate project components to the appropriate cross-functional DRIs (Directly Responsible Individuals). You will be responsible for removing or escalating roadblocks to ensure project timelines are achieved.
Cross-Functional Collaboration: Serve as the key operational liaison between regional Sales, Marketing, Product, and Customer Support teams. You will gather requirements, manage timelines, and act as the key communicator to leadership, ensuring alignment on company goals. This is essential for aligning product strategy with overall business goals and ensuring that products are successfully launched and commercialized.
Market Research: Conduct targeted market research to understand the local hospitality tech industry, customer pain points, and competitive landscape, informing product and GTM adjustments.
Data-Driven Insights: Dive deep into our data to uncover hidden trends, analyze product adoption, and monitor competitive dynamics. You will be responsible for developing dashboards, KPIs, and reports that translate complex data into compelling narratives and actionable recommendations.
Process Improvement: Identify inefficiencies and opportunities for process optimization across the APAC business. You will design, implement, and document new workflows to enhance operational performance and scalability.
Risk Management: Anticipate and proactively manage obstacles and risks to strategic projects, developing mitigation strategies to keep initiatives on track.
Who You Are

Experienced Operator: 3-5 years of experience in project management, consulting, strategy & operations, preferably within a high-growth technology, SaaS, or hospitality environment.
Autonomous Owner: You take ownership of projects, work autonomously, and demonstrate initiative to drive change. You are skilled at identifying issues, assessing risks, and finding creative, pragmatic solutions.You complete day-to-day tasks without instruction and require only general guidance on new or more complex types of work. 
Expert Project Manager: Proven track record of managing initiatives of medium complexity that require a high level of accuracy and dependability. You can manage multiple priorities simultaneously in a fast-paced environment.
Data Analysis: An analytical mindset with proven experience in data analysis and financial modeling. You can translate raw data into actionable insights and strategic recommendations.
A plus: Proficiency in SQL and data visualization tools (e.g., Looker, Tableau).
Financial Modeling Experience: The ability to create financial models to evaluate potential opportunities.
Exceptional Communicator: Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills, with the ability to influence and align cross-functional teams without direct authority.
Tech-Savvy: Proficiency in productivity software (e.g., Google Workspace, Microsoft Office, Salesforce).
Customer Centric: Deep sense of empathy for user challenges and pain points.
About DoorDash


At DoorDash, our mission to empower local economies shapes how our team members move quickly, learn, and reiterate in order to make impactful decisions that display empathy for our range of users—from Dashers to merchant partners to consumers. We are a technology and logistics company that started with door-to-door delivery, and we are looking for team members who can help us go from a company that is known for delivering food to a company that people turn to for any and all goods.

DoorDash is growing rapidly and changing constantly, which gives our team members the opportunity to share their unique perspectives, solve new challenges, and own their careers. We're committed to supporting employees’ happiness, healthiness, and overall well-being by providing comprehensive benefits and perks.

Our Commitment to Diversity and Inclusion


We’re committed to growing and empowering a more inclusive community within our company, industry, and cities. That’s why we hire and cultivate diverse teams of people from all backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. We believe that true innovation happens when everyone has room at the table and the tools, resources, and opportunity to excel.
